-- Intesa Sanpaolo agrees to sell a stake in NH Hoteles
-- 
-- Mon May 26, 2014 12:24PM EDT
-- None



MILAN, May 26 (Reuters) - Intesa Sanpaolo <ISP.MI> said on Monday it agreed to sell a stake in Spain's NH Hoteles <NHH.MC> for 132.7 million euros ($181.2 million) through a share sale and purchase agreement with China's HNA Group.

After the transaction is completed, Italy's biggest retail bank will hold 7.6 percent of the Spanish hotels group, Intesa said in a statement. The agreement is between Intesa Sanpaolo on one side and HNA, parent company of Chinese airline Hainan Airlines <600221.SS>, and its fully-owned special purpose vehicle Tangla Spain on the other, Intesa said.